title: All types dialog shows obfuscated classes
description: The Open Type dialog in the application displays the obfuscated classes from JDK 1.4. These classes, such as 'a', 'a1', 'b', 'c', and 'd', are shown prominently in the dialog.
OB: The obfuscated classes are currently very visible in the Open Type dialog.
EB: The obfuscated classes should be less prominent in the Open Type dialog.
SR: To reproduce the issue, open the application and navigate to the Open Type dialog. Observe how the obfuscated classes from JDK 1.4 are displayed prominently.
